Kuntze, Revis. Gen. Pl. 2: 711. 1891, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">nomen rejiciendum</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="112">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Colenso" authorityYear="1885" class="Liliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia albicans" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albicans">Astelia albicans</taxonomicName>
Colenso, Trans. &amp; Proc. New Zealand Inst. 17: 252. 1885. Type: NEW ZEALAND. North Island. East slopes of Ruahine mountain range, county of Waipawa. Jan. 1884, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">A. Hamilton s.n.</emphasis>
(Syntype: K [000524880, digital image!], staminate, pistillate). 
<bibRefCitation author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg (1934</bibRefCitation>
, 88) identified a single specimen at K as the type material and the specimen in his plate 20 (K000524880) is consistent with the specimen described as the type. As 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Astelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is dioecious, the inclusion of one staminate and one pistillate inflorescence on the specimen means that it represents two distinct collections and each is rendered a syntype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="112">
<taxonomicName authority="Willd." authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Colenso" class="Liliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Funckia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Funckia albicans" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albicans">Funckia albicans</taxonomicName>
Kuntze, Revis. Gen. Pl. 2: 711. 1891, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">nomen rejiciendum</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
