<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="112" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="112">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia microsperma" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Astelia microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Colenso based on a specimen at Kew that contained material from two species (
<bibRefCitation author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg 1934</bibRefCitation>
). The species description &quot;referred to both, but mainly to the pistillate raceme in the envelope&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg 1934</bibRefCitation>
, 82). 
<bibRefCitation author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg (1934)</bibRefCitation>
lectotypified the fruiting material in the packet (K000524879) as the type material of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia microsperma" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Astelia microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as syn. 
<taxonomicName authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Skottsberg" authorityYear="1934" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum microspermum" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microspermum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Collospermum microspermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and determined the remaining material on the specimen (K000524882) as 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia hastata" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Astelia hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as syn. 
<taxonomicName authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Birch" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum hastatum" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hastatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Collospermum hastatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="113" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" type="excluded species">
