<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="112">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Colenso" authorityYear="1882" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia spicata" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spicata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Astelia spicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Colenso, Trans. &amp; Proc. New Zealand Inst. 14: 335. 1882, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">nomen illegitimum</emphasis>
. Type: NEW ZEALAND. North Island. In the forests about Kopua and Norsewood, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Colenso</emphasis>
. (Lectotype: K [000524878, digital image!], pistillate, designated by Skottsberg, 1934, 81). 
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, LB" journalOrPublisher="New Zealand Journal of Botany" pageId="12" pageNumber="117" pagination="201 - 240" publicationUrl="10.1080/0028825X.1966.10429041" refId="B17" refString="Moore, LB, 1966. Australasian asteliads (Liliaceae). New Zealand Journal of Botany 4 (2): 201 - 240, DOI: 10.1080/0028825X.1966.10429041" title="Australasian asteliads (Liliaceae)." url="10.1080/0028825X.1966.10429041" volume="4" year="1966">Moore (1966)</bibRefCitation>
regarded the type and other specimens examined to represent very small individuals of either 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia hastata" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Astelia hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia microsperma" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Astelia microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="112">
<taxonomicName authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Skottsb" authorityYear="1934" baseAuthorityName="Colenso" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum spicatum" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spicatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Collospermum spicatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Colenso) Skottsb., Kongl. Svenska Vetensk. Acad. Handl. Ser. 3, 14(2): 80. 1934; based on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Colenso" authorityYear="1882" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia spicata" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spicata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Astelia spicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Colenso 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">nomen illegitimum</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carse" authorityYear="1927" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia nana" order="Asparagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
<pageBreakToken pageId="8" pageNumber="113" start="start">Astelia</pageBreakToken>
nana
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Carse, Trans. &amp; Proc. New Zealand Inst. 57: 91. 1926, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">nomen illegitimum</emphasis>
. Type: NEW ZEALAND. North Island. Kaiaka (Mangonui County), Maungatapere (Whangarei County), Mauku (Franklin County), 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">H. Carse s.n.</emphasis>
; synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Colenso" authorityYear="1882" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia spicata" order="Asparagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spicata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">Astelia spicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Colenso 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">nomen illegitimum</emphasis>
. This is regarded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg (1934)</bibRefCitation>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Colenso" authorityYear="1882" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia spicata" order="Asparagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spicata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">Astelia spicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Colenso 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">nomen illegitimum</emphasis>
. (Syntypes: CHR [328212, digital image!], staminate, pistillate; [328213, digital image!), pistillate; AK [3227!], pistillate; [3228!], pistillate; [222913!], staminate; [303282!], pistillate).
</paragraph>
